time complexity: O(log(n))
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW

Explanation:

The solution iterates through the digits of the number n using a while loop. For each digit, it calculates the sign based on its position in the number and adds it to the sum. The sign is determined by checking if the digit is less than 0, and multiplying it by -1 or 1 accordingly. The number is divided by 10 in each iteration to remove the last digit. The time complexity is O(log(n)) because the loop iterates log(n) times, where n is the number of digits in n. The space complexity is O(1) because the algorithm uses a constant amount of space for the sum variable. The energy implications are low because the algorithm does not require any additional resources beyond the standard C++ runtime.

